    <item>
      <title>Chart: Sentences for knife carrying are increasing, but not for teens</title>
      <link>http://lesscrime.info/post/knife-sentencing/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://lesscrime.info/post/knife-sentencing/</guid>
      <description>


&lt;p&gt;Sentences for carrying a bladed or pointed article have become more severe for adults over the past decade, with 41% of men now going to prison on conviction. For younger offenders, the picture is different: half of girls and a third of boys caught with a knife receive no penalty – a proportion that is largely unchanged since 2008 – while fewer than one in ten receive a custodial sentence.&lt;/p&gt;
